<blockquote>
<h6 id="toc14"><span>IR#20██011300███-12, Status: <em>Replied.</em> User: <em>tthomp03</em> (<strong>IP:</strong> 10.101.147.███) Timestamp: <em>20██/01/13&#160;13:20</em></span></h6>
<p>Hi Larry. That's a bit premature, SCUTTLE is resilient and it won't do anything bad without several weeks with no check-ins. If it was working last week we have until Valentine's Day at the earliest. We'll get it taken care of. Brandon, the snapshots look fine as far as I can see, you're set to try a reversion at 1700. Be prepared for a long evening, those can take a while if you haven't done one on a system that old. I can't force a current snapshot so get a system image before you do anything on the ground. Terry.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<blockquote>
<h6 id="toc15"><span>IR#20██011300███-13, Status: <em>Replied.</em> User: <em>bcolli01</em> (<strong>IP:</strong> 10.101.147.███) Timestamp: <em>20██/01/13&#160;13:42</em></span></h6>
